Well, I found the history recorded in Second King's very interesting.

00:00:32.179 --> 00:00:39.179
In Chapter 15, verse 4, it says that under King Aziraya, the high places were not removed,

00:00:39.179 --> 00:00:44.179
and the people were still sacrificing and making sacrificial smoke on the high places.

00:00:44.179 --> 00:00:50.179
So Judah had a good king, but the nation was still steeped in false worship.

00:00:50.179 --> 00:00:53.179
It seems that Joel prophesied during that time.

00:00:53.179 --> 00:00:55.179
I wonder what that was like.

00:00:55.179 --> 00:00:57.179
I thought about the high places too.

00:00:57.179 --> 00:01:03.179
The inside book, under the heading high places, says that they could be found not only on hills and mountains,

00:01:03.179 --> 00:01:08.180
but also in the valleys, in stream beds and cities, and under the trees,

00:01:08.180 --> 00:01:14.180
and that frequently those high places were scenes of disgusting sexual practices,

00:01:14.180 --> 00:01:18.180
including ceremonial prostitution and child sacrifice.

00:01:18.180 --> 00:01:21.180
No wonder Jehovah hated false worship.

00:01:22.180 --> 00:01:29.180
It must have pained him so much to watch his own people deliberately engage in a decade after decade.

00:01:29.180 --> 00:01:33.180
I wonder how Joel felt seeing this taking place all around him.

00:01:33.180 --> 00:01:38.180
How many people did he personally know who were affected by this false worship?

00:01:38.180 --> 00:01:43.180
Maybe he wondered where the nation was headed, and how long Jehovah was going to put up with it.

00:01:43.180 --> 00:01:46.180
Well, he didn't have to wonder indefinitely.

00:01:46.180 --> 00:01:53.180
Jehovah takes action, and he gives Joel this vivid prophecy about the awe-inspiring day of Jehovah.

00:01:53.180 --> 00:01:55.180
Imagine what that must have been like.

00:01:55.180 --> 00:01:59.180
The locust swarms that invade and strip the beautiful land of Judah bear,

00:01:59.180 --> 00:02:07.180
the clouds and thick gloom, the sun and moon turning dark, and then complete restoration.

00:02:07.180 --> 00:02:09.180
Wow.

00:02:09.180 --> 00:02:13.180
That must have been so moving for Joel.

00:02:13.180 --> 00:02:20.180
Jehovah gave Joel an outstanding glimpse of the discipline and the restoration that was in store for Israel.

00:02:20.180 --> 00:02:26.180
This must have been so reassuring to Joel, and it must have greatly affected the way he delivered that message.

00:02:26.180 --> 00:02:34.180
Think about this. It's possible that Joel was the very first prophet that Jehovah told about that great day.

